<TEXT>
twentythree years after they were 
first used in vietnam combat hunterkiller helicopter tactics 
are being updated with the latest in nightflying technology and 
interservice cooperation 
as darkness fell monday over the desert a small army oh58 
scout helicopter loaded with special gear for night operations 
lifted off from an airbase runway 
just behind it came two of the marine corps newest ah1 cobras 
the whiskey model that has twice the power and three times the 
lethal punch of its indochinaera ancestor 
earlier in the day the pilots sat together for a briefing on 
the nights twohour training mission 
together the pilots from the armys 82nd airborne division and 
marine light attack squadron 269 formed a hunterkiller team 
designed to destroy enemy tanks before the tanks are aware of their 
presence 
the technique was first developed in vietnam where army pink 
teams combined a scout helicopter to find enemy bunker complexes 
and jungle camps with a cobra gunship to destroy them with rockets 
and machine guns 
if war with iraq breaks out officers said the technique will 
be applied to baghdads tank formations in the open desert where 
us forces expect to have a wide edge in nightvision capability 
and weaponry 
this is a perfect environment over here we re working 
specifically to fly in that environment specifically to fly at 
night because that is probably what were going to be called on to 
do said lt col kenneth hill of tulsa okla commander of the 
marine air unit 
the army helicopters are the result of years of effort to 
develop an aircraft for special operations in darkness 
they were first used for night patrol duty during the persian 
gulf tanker war in 198788 
one pilot told then of hovering within easy view of fishing 
boats whose occupants were unaware of his presence 
they never look up he said 
the cobras sitting on the saudi flightline are the latest 
models all less than a year old 
their engines produce about 3300 horsepower twice that of the 
vietnam version they carry laserguided hellfire missiles and 
other weapons that were less sophisticated or nonexistent in 
indochina days 
