absolutely ridiculous and said any such program would be 
carried out by a trusted charitable agency such as the 
international committee of the red cross 
over the past several weeks us and united nations emissaries 
have failed to convince angolan authorities to show more 
flexibility 
the famine area has been afflicted both by drought and by 
prolonged fighting that resulted from a government offensive 
earlier this year 
the administration is prepared to be the major contributor if 
the angolan government agrees to an international relief effort 
officials said 
angola has been a sore point in eastwest relations for years 
while the united states has been supplying the rebels the soviet 
union and cuba have provided generous backing for the government 
cuba once had 50000 troops in angola but has begun a phased 
withdrawal that is expected to be completed next year 
one measure of the mistrust between the angolan government and 
unita was the breakdown of peace talks last week in lisbon 
portugal 
the negotiations collapsed after government negotiators refused 
a rebel demand for formal political recognition in advance of any 
ceasefire agreement 
this inflexible demand was designed intentionally to scuttle 
ceasefire negotiations said manuel pedro pacavira angolas 
un ambassador 
