to 242 percent at the same time rural households experienced 
less crime with only 172 percent suffering compared with 18 
percent in 1988 
the portion of households with incomes of 15000 and above that 
suffered from a crime edged downward last year while crime hit a 
larger portion of households with lower incomes than it had in 
1988 still the households with the highest target rate 27 
percent were those with incomes of 25000 or more 
