<TEXT>
at least 40 blacks were killed 
in savage township fighting including 11 who died when soldiers 
fired assault rifles today on a crowd at a migrant workers hostel 
police said 
the latest violence came as president fw de klerk and african 
national congress leader nelson mandela toured the townships to 
call for an end to the black factional fighting that has killed 
more than 550 people in the past three weeks 
the worst fighting occurred in sebokeng south of johannesburg 
where police said they entered a migrant workers hostel to 
investigate the deaths of four men believed to be township 
residents abducted by the hostel dwellers 
an armed mob of up to 5000 gathered outside the hostel saying 
they wanted to launch a revenge attack on zulus inside police said 
when the mob refused to disperse army troops were called in and 
a shooting incident occurred said police col frans malherbe 
he said 11 bodies were found after the mob dispersed 
malherbe said both the police and military were investigating 
the shooting 
township resident n khumalo said the soldiers took up a 
position cocked their guns i thought maybe they wanted to scare 
the people 
all of a sudden there was shooting many of the people ran 
some of the people fell khumalo was quoted as saying by the 
independent south african press association 
police said 36 people were killed in various clashes today in 
sebokeng they reported four deaths overnight in vosloorus and 
katlehong southeast of johannesburg witnesses said several more 
people were killed in the two townships but the deaths could not 
be confirmed 
they also said they arrested 150 men in connection with the 
earlier violence in the hostel and confiscated four ak47 assault 
rifles 
