said he will plead guilty to accepting a 2000 cash bribe from 
cobb 
state reps robert kohn luther taylor and danny winstead along 
with brown and lee were indicted under the hobbs act a federal 
law banning acceptance of money or gifts in return for votes or 
favors winstead also was indicted on a second charge of 
obstruction of justice 
all five defendants were required to plead innocent last week 
because federal magistrates cannot accept guilty pleas 
kohn a republican who has said he will not seek reelection 
and taylor a democrat have been suspended from the house 
winstead a republican resigned his seat on aug 23 
taylor indicted on six counts faces a maximum sentence of 120 
years in prison and a 15 million fine if convicted winstead 
faces a total of 30 years in prison and a 500000 fine if 
