<TEXT>
he didnt make it to historic 
kitty hawk but pilot eric raymond on tuesday celebrated the first 
transcontinental flight in a solarpowered plane by going sailing 
i hope this will help enlighten people to the potential of 
solar power and alternative energy sources raymond said of his 
2467mile flight 
raymond 33 said winds prevented a kitty hawk landing but were 
good for sailboarding 
raymonds sun seeker ultralight aircraft was safe from the wind 
in a shed at the farm he landed monday nine miles short of the 
wright brothers memorial 
if i had an hour more time monday i could have made it in 
raymond said as he relaxed on a beach not far from kitty hawk 
where the wright brothers pioneered powered flight 
low visibility rain and unfavorable wind forced him to land at 
the farm near the community of spot about 500 yards from currituck 
sound which separates the mainland from the offshore barrier 
island where kitty hawk and kill devil hills are located 
the sun seeker depends on sunshine and favorable wind solar 
cells produce power for its electric motor which is used for 
takeoffs and landings after takeoff the plane rides thermals 
columns of rising warm air like a glider 
raymond said tuesdays 35 mph northeasterly gusts would create 
turbulence around the trees surrounding the airstrip at the wright 
memorial 
i wouldnt want to land there with more than 10 or 12 mph 
winds he said 
raymond said the trip took a bit longer than i expected but 
thats because it was against the wind i expected to have 
prevailing westerlies but instead it was more easterly 
two weeks was raymonds goal for completing the trip but wind 
and weather delays stretched the trip to 32 days including 23 days 
in the air he took off from desert center calif about 200 miles 
east of los angeles 
raymond said the rigors of flying and the attraction of the 
beach and good sailboarding weather were enough to call him off 
work for a day 
he said he liked sailboarding because you have a clean 
endless source of energy you can wind surf at 30 mph all day long 
i like anything thats natural like that that doesnt pollute 
he said he would set his plane up for people to see wednesday 
before driving home to california 
his father sam raymond said hes glad the trip is over 
