their decision 
on july 20 they ordered a witness by witness hearing to 
determine if the evidence against north had been influenced by the 
testimony he gave congress about the irancontra affair under a 
limited grant of immunity from prosecution 
that socalled use immunity grant barred walsh from using 
norths testimony as evidence in a criminal prosecution 
but walsh called the panels order an unwarranted extension of 
use immunity protection that was particularly unjustified 
because his office took special precautions to ensure that 
prosecutors were not exposed to norths testimony 
