the submarine named the sea cliff is a 31foot 58000pound 
craft able to operate at depths up to 20000 feet it carries a 
threemember crew 
the submarine and its support ship are capable of retrieving 
objects from the ocean floor stairs said 
stairs said searchers will take pictures of the debris and let 
authorities decide whether it is worth retrieving 
the sea cliff left san diego on tuesday and is expected to 
arrive at pearl harbor on sept 11 stairs said 
united flight 811 carried 355 passengers when it left honolulu 
for new zealand on feb 24 1989 
the cargo door opened at 22000 feet tearing away a section of 
fuselage nine people were swept to their deaths and five other 
suffered serious injuries the crew managed to return the jet to 
honolulu 
the ntsb inquiry determined that faulty design of the locking 
mechanism probably caused a cockpit light to falsely indicate the 
door was locked 
the agency blamed united boeing co and the federal aviation 
administration for failing to correct problems with the door 
</TEXT>
