secretary of state james a baker iii said 
tuesday the bush administration is giving preliminary thought to 
creating a natotype organization to deal with future security 
threats to the persian gulf 
at the same time baker said iraq has been restored to the list 
of countries which the united states accuses of engaging in 
international terrorism 
