washington post reporter caryle murphy 
willingly traveled to kuwait in late july to cover an unfolding 
international news event she escaped a month later holding 
preciously to her stories and her life 
when murphy arrived in kuwait city iraqi president saddam 
hussein was amassing thousands of troops from his millionman army 
along the iraqikuwaiti border but still promising he would take 
no military action against his tiny neighbor 
in the early morning hours of on aug 2 a week after murphys 
arrival iraqi soldiers quickly rolled over kuwait 
one failed escape attempt and 25 days later murphy arrived in 
saudi arabia after a tense journey across the desert 
the journalist related her trials in a lengthy article published 
in the washington post 
despite the turmoil in kuwait after the invasion murphy said 
she hadnt expected to be trapped 
like most foreigners i assumed that in a few days time 
the borders would be open for those who wanted to leave and that 
the exodus would start but it never happened she wrote 
murphy recalled that she and two other western journalists spent 
the first week after the invasion conducting interviews on the 
streets in hospitals and over the telephone as if we were 
covering any story however she soon discovered that there was 
no way to dispatch material to her newspaper 
after leaving her hotel to live with an american family murphy 
decided to flee the country as the two other journalists already 
had done 
murphy and two other americans set out by car on the morning of 
aug 14 they were back in kuwait city 90 minutes later after being 
turned back by iraqi soldiers 
but murphy decided to try again after she learned of a convoy 
that was planning to leave 
i decided in a minute mostly by instinct i reasoned that the 
worst that could happen was that i would be detained if the iraqis 
spotted me she wrote 
nearly seven hours later murphy arrived at the saudi border 
there she learned from a us diplomat that she was the first 
american to arrive at the outpost in eight days 
