<TEXT>
internal affairs paramount home video vhsbeta no 
suggested retail price rated r 
the men and women who police the police are the lowest of the 
low to their fellow officers pariahs scum hitlers in blue but 
the feeling is more than mutual 
in mike figgis internal affairs the clash of wills and 
collision of ethics come barreling to a bloody and shattering 
conclusion for detective raymond avila and dennis peck the 
celebrated street cop he brings down 
avila andy garcia is a methodical and eager cop who gets 
promoted to the internal affairs division of the los angeles 
police he believes in his job and he believes in the law his 
partner amy laurie metcalf is a careful investigator who goes 
by the book and who understands that all their job means is a shot 
at becoming a lieutenant 
a routine investigation of excessive violence in an arrest by 
another police officer leads the pair to suspect peck of being the 
mastermind behind a complicated network of crime ranging from 
murder to extortion to prostitution to money laundering and fraud 
peck richard gere is a master manipulator who knows what 
buttons to push to get a desired reaction from people and thus set 
plans to his liking hes also a loathesome misogynist and racist 
he and avila lock horns and peck finding avilas achilles 
heel plays a psychological game that involves avilas wife 
kathleen nancy travis 
after a memorable bit in the untouchables as the fed who 
lines up a killing shot while stretched out at an impossible angle 
on a staircase and teaming with michael douglas as a cop in 
black rain garcia has landed his first starring role but 
theres more to this actor than cop roles his smoldering good 
looks quiet manner and intensity hold promise for greater things 
to come 
hes convincing as avila revealing his hot latin passions 
vulnerabilities and quiet pursuit of the law less convincing is 
gere who gives a onenote performance that erupts at the end in 
almost comic book frenzy 
figgis uneven pacing and reliance on blood and guts makes this 
a difficult movie to watch on the home screen 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
heart condition rcacolumbia home video vhsbeta 8995 
rated r 
is racism the stuff that comedy is made of can bigotry get a 
laugh or two as writer and director james d parriott has 
borrowed freely from the hollywood movie mill to craft his film 
about a heart transplant sex drugs and politics a coverup and 
murder and the improbable relationship between a black ghost and a 
bigoted white cop 
unfortunately parriott whose work has been limited to 
televison six million dollar man island sons from here 
to eternity brings a tv mentality to heart condition with 
quickfix sight gags and jokes you can almost imagine a laugh 
track 
he has all the standard characters a prostitute with a heart of 
gold a classy lawyer who works for gangsters a seedy and bigoted 
vice cop a slick pimp a police captain who spends most of his 
time playing golf 
theres also the standard story line a highpowered senator 
dies while having sex and drugs with two hookers theres a 
coverup and the silencing of those who knew or might have known 
and who is to solve the dastardly deed the seedy bigoted vice cop 
with a brand new heart 
napoleon stone denzel washington is a successful lawyer whose 
clients include highclass hookers including crystal chloe webb 
the former girlfriend of vice cop jack moony bob hoskins 
crystal a camera fanatic snapped pictures during the lustdrug 
romp with the senator and gave the film to moony for safe keeping 
the senators death is listed as a heart attack and the two hookers 
are under the watchful eye of the pimp who arranged the date 
certain washington politicos think crystal might have told her 
lawyer about the incident so they kill him 
meanwhile moony a lover of junk food fat and liquor has a 
heart attack and will die unless given a new heart he gets stones 
heart he also gets stones ghost a dapper gent who has a change 
of clothes in just about every scene 
where have we seen all of this before lets see the heart 
transplant recalls that raymond st jacquesleslie nielsen 
blaxploitation flick a change of mind in which a white 
district attorneys brain is transplanted into a black mans body 
the ghost part is easy all those wonderful topper movies 
with roland young only heart condition lacks the unspoiled 
sophistication of the kirbys ghostly existence as for the sleazy 
white copblack man buddy movie theres 48 hrs with nick 
nolte and eddie murphy 
there are some fun moments though moony walking along with his 
arm around the ghosts shoulder getting puzzled looks from 
passersby theres also a funny bit when stone tries to stop moony 
from eating a hamburger dripping with grease and cheese the scene 
has hoskins wrestling a hamburger to the ground before stunned 
lunchers shades of roger rabbit 
after a while moony actually starts to like stone gets the bad 
guys wins back crystal and helps her raise the baby she and stone 
had unfortunately this could be the perfect setup for a sequel 
hoskins and washington are both topflight actors who are 
versatile enough to handle high drama washington in glory and 
a soldiers story hoskins in mona lisa and a prayer for 
the dying as well as comedy washington in carbon copy and 
hoskins in who framed roger rabbit they handle the script and 
the story with grace there also are excellent support performances 
by webb and roger e mosley as capt wendt 
in heart condition the laughs are indeed there but there 
are also too many slow pockets and the movie is also just a tad 
too derivative 
still its not a bad diversion for a lazy friday night vidfest 
