the government is awarding a 15 million 
grant to the visiting nurse association of america for a national 
demonstration program in an effort to increase home health care to 
frail older people 
the association is seeking aid from foundations and corporations 
to match the grant provided by action the federal domestic 
volunteer agency 
the project is intended to get the private sector involved in 
helping people live independently 
with the matching financing the visiting nurse association will 
organize volunteer jobs for 200 senior citizens who will visit with 
400 frail elderly and help them remain in their homes rather than 
be moved to institutions 
known as senior companions the program will provide the 
lowincome volunteers aged 60 and older with training a small 
allowance reimbursement for transportation and meals insurance 
and an annual physical examination 
the threeyear project will be conducted in 18 communities 
throughout the country locations are to be announced later 
