<TEXT>
fujitsu japans largest computer maker announced 
a powerful new mainframe computer tuesday that it says is the 
fastest in the world the news came a day before rival ibm is 
expected announce its new topoftheline models 
both companies are depending on their newgeneration mainframes 
to maintain their technological and competitive leadership in 
highend computers 
international business machines corp has refused to release 
details of its new computer line before its announcement scheduled 
for wednesday 
fujitsu officials said the top model in their new m1800 series 
is capable of executing up to 600 million instructions per second 
or mips in scientific calculations 
analysts say the new ibm topoftheline computer codenamed 
the summit will run at a maximum speed of about 230 mips the most 
powerful current ibm mainframe can handle about 112 mips 
however ibm the worlds largest computer company is expected 
to announce that customers will be able to link several of the new 
models together to boost power dramatically perhaps exceeding 600 
mips 
toshio hiraguri general manager of fujitsus computer systems 
group said the 600 mips figure doesnt adequately represent 
typical operating conditions under which he said the m1800 series 
would run even faster 
unlike supercomputers which are designed to make repetitive 
scientific calculations mainframes must be able to handle a wide 
range of general business data base and communications information 
often at the same time 
we believe fujitsus mainframe will be competitive not just 
today but also tomorrow a company official said referring to 
ibms expected announcement 
nec in july announced a mainframe that it says is capable of 500 
mips but it uses a different operating system than the system 
shared by ibm fujitsu and hitachi making a direct comparison of 
processing speeds difficult the operating system is the base layer 
of software that controls internal computer functions 
hitachi in june announced it will build a mainframe capable of 
155 mips 
fujitsus m1800 series speed comes in part from special 
highspeed logic and memory chips highcapacity fiberoptic 
interconnections and sophisticated batch processing of data the 
company said the topoftheline model 85 also will be the first 
mainframe in the world with eight processors it said 
the new ibm computers will have similar features except the top 
model will have only six processors analysts say 
fujitsu officials denied that they timed their announcement 
tuesday to reduce the impact of ibms news conference in the united 
states 
weve been planning to begin shipments next april and our 
customers have been asking us to make the announcement as soon as 
possible a fujitsu official said so its just a coincidence 
that ibm decided to announce its computer at about the same time 
ibm officials declined to comment tuesday on fujitsus 
announcement the us company depends on sales of mainframes and 
associated software and equipment for about half its annual profit 
fujitsu said it plans to sell about 300 of the 
multimilliondollar systems over the next three years with most 
sales likely to be in japan the computers also will be sold 
overseas under the nameplate of siemens ag the west german 
computer company and their technology is likely to appear in 
mainframes produced by amdahl corp a us maker of ibmcompatible 
mainfames that is 45 percent owned by fujitsu 
amdahl and hitachi generally have undercut ibms mainframe 
prices and have eaten into its sales in recent years although ibm 
still has about 87 percent of the us highend mainframe market 
says computer intelligence a california research firm 
some industry analysts have predicted a declining market for 
large generalservice mainframes saying customers would be better 
off buying increasingly sophisticated smaller computer workstations 
that can be tailored to specific functions 
several of the new fujitsu machines however can be linked 
together with each handling separate functions such as data base 
processing communications and application processing to customize 
and maximize performance the company said 
with this announcement we want to say that the mainframe 
business is not dead said a fujitsu official speaking on 
condition of anonymity they will continue to be the main anchor 
for customers whether they be researchers or businesses 
fujitsu said it expects to sell most of its m1800 systems to 
financial institutions research institutes government 
organizations and engineering facilities 
