<TEXT>
the number of working oil and natural gas rigs in 
the united states rose again this week climbing by 10 to 1012 
baker hughes inc reported 
a week ago the count had increased by 15 to total 1002 the 
count a year ago this week was 936 baker hughes said tuesday 
the houstonbased oil toolmaker company has kept track of the 
rig count the widely watched index of drilling activity since 
1940 the count represents the number of rigs actively exploring 
for oil not those producing oil 
ike kerridge keeper of the count at baker hughes said tuesday 
that the increase in oil prices caused by the middle east crisis 
probably is beginning to have some positive impact on the rig count 
some of the count increase may be a reflection of higher 
prices although it is the season when the count goes up 
anyway kerridge said and the increase have been modest but 
if the middle east crisis hasnt begun to affect it yet i think 
it will very shortly 
kerridge said there is no absolute way to judge exactly how 
rising oil prices affects the domestic rig count 
at the height of the oil boom in december 1981 the rig count 
