gallon up 583 cents the expiring september contract had gained 
035 cent on friday 
higher oil prices which are a harbinger of higher inflation 
sent bond prices lower in other markets stock prices were mixed 
with the dow jones average of 30 industrials falling less than a 
point in currency dealings the dollar slumped 
even in the absence of significant developments in the persian 
gulf analysts had expected energy futures prices to spike higher 
following a sharp advance in london on monday 
traders turned their attention to the basic supply and demand 
balances said oil analyst jim murchie of sanford c bernstein amp 
co things are quiet enough now for people to go back and do the 
basic work 
present oil supplies may not meet demand for the chilly fourth 
quarter murchie said adding that half the worlds oil is used for 
heating in the last quarter of the year oil stocks are typically 
drawn down to meet heightened demand 
before the crisis we were expecting a 1 to 15 million barrel 
a day drawdown now were projecting a 2 to 25 million barrels a 
day to meet fourthquarter demand murchie said 
the organization of petroleum exporting countries recent 
agreement to increase its daily crude production quota to 225 
million barrels daily still falls short of projected fourthquarter 
demand murchie said 
during a crisis those who hold oil contracts are reluctant to 
sell which pushes the price higher experts said there was a lack 
of sellers on tuesday which was responsible for the rise in prices 
amid moderate volume 
the market also was weighed down by disappointment over the slow 
release of hostages by iraq and the unsuccessful attempts by united 
