<TEXT>
like the mythical icarus with his waxen wings 
ernest saunders was a high flier who crashed 
the former chief executive of guinness plc who earned 740000 
the year he engineered what was then britains largest corporate 
takeover has lost his job his wealth and finally his freedom 
his wife suffered a nervous breakdown and remains far away in 
switzerland all he has left is the loyalty of his three children 
and an unshakable insistence that he is innocent 
references to icarus cropped up in several newspapers late last 
month as saunders began a 5year jail term for organizing an 
illegal operation to ensure guinness successful takeover of 
distillers ltd a scottish whisky and gin maker 
judge sir denis henry summed up saunders as a very determined 
and singleminded man used to getting your own way and relentless 
in pursuit of it 
gerald ronson 51 chief of heron international plc and former 
stockbroker anthony parnes 44 were given 12 months and 2 years 
respectively for their part in the affair ronson also was fined a 
record 985 million 
financier sir jack lyons 74 convicted with them will be 
sentenced sept 25 
the four were found guilty of 19 charges ranging from stock 
manipulation and theft to false accounting in guinness hardfought 
504 billion takeover bid for distillers in 1986 
the court found the four had illegally inflated the price of 
guinness stock making the companys bid more attractive than a 
rival offer from the argyll supermarket group 
during the sixmonth trial at southwark crown court saunders 
54 denied knowing about any illegal payments to buyers of guinness 
stock 
but he said he had encouraged people institutions anyone i 
met to sell distillers shares to guinness rather than to argyll 
and to buy guinness shares because that was my job 
during seven days of testimony saunders testily defended his 
integrity characterizing the governments allegations as 
scurrilous disgraceful and disgusting 
benjamin guinness the chairman of the family brewing enterprise 
founded in dublin in 1759 had hired saunders in 1981 to reverse 
the companys falling fortunes and thats just what he did 
starting in june 1984 guinness expanded vigorously buying a 
chain of newsagencies the champneys group of health clubs 
natures best health products and the cranks health food restaurant 
chain 
in 1985 guinness quietly took over the scottish whisky makers 
arthur bell and sons 
between 1981 and 1985 guinness pretax profits rose to 170 
million from 823 million 
james saunders said guinness value on the stock market jumped 
to 56 billion by 1986 from 168 million in 1981 
but within a year of clinching the takeover of distillers in 
1986 saunders was out of a job and in police custody charged in 
britains biggest financial scandal 
he had been known in the city londons financial district 
as a brilliant marketing man and when trouble broke observers 
say the marketing man came to the fore 
so was born saunders the scapegoat said the observer a 
london sunday newspaper innocent ernest saunders the chairman 
and chief executive who knew nothing heard nothing and most 
certainly did nothing that could have caused him to face a trial 
this was the hero of nightmare a 270page book written by 
his 24yearold son james the book depicts saunders suffering a 
living hell after his arrest in may 1987 
the man accustomed to limousines rode the subway to court lived 
in a small flat and relied on legal aid to pay for his attorney 
james and his sister joanna 25 often came to court with their 
father saunders codefendants were supported by glamorous wives 
but carole saunders stayed in switzerland where she and her 
husband had gone in 1987 to recover from psychological stress 
the man i knew as energetic logical and lucid a 
perfectionist had changed into an intellectually broken man 
testified dr eric rochat who treated saunders 
saunders colleagues at guinness portrayed him as ambitious 
singleminded sometimes domineering and even ruthless 
olivier roux former guinness finance director said saunders 
was willing to delegate but in the distillers bid where it was 
never comfortable he was involved in all aspects and overseeing 
all aspects 
according to the times of london guinness workers had a 
nickname for ernest saunders they called the boss deadly 
ernest 
two inches taller than 6 feet he was every inch the grayhaired 
patrician with steady gaze and studied courtesy his club was the 
carlton the traditional hideaway for leaders of the conservative 
party 
the image obscured the roots of the man 
born ernst walter schleyer in vienna on oct 21 1935 he was 
the son of uly and hanni schleyer a jewish couple who fled from 
the nazis to england in 1938 
in britain they determined that ernst and his brother peter 
should be brought up as english boys according to james 
saunders ernst schleyer became ernest saunders at age 12 when he 
entered the prestigious st pauls school in london 
