<TEXT>
a paine webber inc account executive was 
fined 125000 and barred from dealing with members of the national 
association of securities dealers the nasd announced tuesday 
the nasd a selfregulating organization empowered by congress 
to oversee the overthecounter securities market also fined paine 
webber and the executives superviser 30000 
both the company and the two individuals settled the charges 
without admitting or denying wrongdoing 
in an unrelated matter the securities and exchange commission 
upheld an nasd disciplinary action against wn whelen amp co a 
georgetown del brokerage for numerous securities rule violations 
in the paine webber case nilda rubiera zim a new york city 
account executive was accused of recommending and executing 
securities transactions without considering if they were suitable 
for her customers financial situation and investment objectives 
in addition to the 125000 zim was barred from association 
with any member of the nasd in any capacity 
the nasd also found that zims superior joseph patrick tota of 
flower hill ny and the firm itself failed to supervise her 
properly the company and tota were fined a total of 30000 and 
tota was suspended from nasd association for five business days 
in the whelen action the sec which has veto power over nasd 
actions upheld a previous decision fining the firm 25000 and 
suspending william n whelen jr the firms president for 10 
business days 
the nasd found that the firm misappropriated assets violated 
rules on net capital and protecting customers investments 
improperly extended credit and other violations 
in upholding the sanctions the sec noted that the firm had a 
history of prior violations and had shown an unwillingness or 
inability to follow the rules 
</TEXT>
