<TEXT>
an owner of a defunct paramusbased 
pennystock firm accused of bilking customers of more than 60 
million pleaded guilty tuesday to a federal racketeering charge 
leonard tucker 30 of boca raton fla faces up to 20 years in 
federal prison and millions of dollars in fines for his part in the 
fd roberts securities inc scam according to a release issued by 
us attorney michael chertoff 
tucker was among eight toplevel fd roberts officials indicted 
by a newark federal grand jury on march 26 
the indictment alleged the eight derived 67 million in illicit 
profits while associated with the pennystock brokerage firm which 
shut down in february 1989 
tucker said he and his codefendants controlled the sale of 
stock placed stock in illegal accounts controlled the public 
companies whose stock they sold and used collusive brokerage firms 
according to chertoff 
tucker also said he recruited individuals with little or no 
securities experience to be salespeople and condoned the use of 
deceptive and misleading telephone sales techniques chertoff said 
also charged in the march indictment and awaiting trial are fred 
galiardo of daytona beach fla john perfetti of bayville ny 
alan lieb of pine brook john montondo of boca raton and three of 
tuckers relatives brothers daniel tucker of boca raton and gary 
tucker of new york and stepfather richard thaw of boca raton 
</TEXT>
